remediation.secondary:
If PHP serialization must be retained, use unserialize()'s $allowed_classes parameter to restrict which classes can be instantiated:
$this->backup = unserialize($importData['data'], [
    'allowed_classes' => [
        'Nextend\\SmartSlider3\\BackupSlider\\BackupData',
        // ... exact list of expected classes
    ]
]);
PHP 7.0+ supports this option. Classes not in the allowlist are instantiated as __PHP_Incomplete_Class.
